The paper deals with approximation algorithms for the Travelling Salesman Problem, which is a classic problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The focus of the paper is on the special case of graphic metrics, which involves graphs and their properties, making categories such as computational geometry (cs.CG) and graph theory (cs.GT) likely as well. The paper also involves analysis of bounds and approximation factors, which could fall under categories such as discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and computational complexity (cs.CC).
